                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#74r">Fol. 74r</locus>: Rhymed supplication for the soul of a local scribe Wäldä Muse.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 74r: እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላክነ፡ ዘአንሃልከ፨ ቅድመ፡ ጥቅማ፡ ለኢያሪኮ፡ በእደ፡ ኢያሱ፡ ገብርከ፨ ከማሁ፡ {ይእዜ፡} አንህል፡ ጥቅመ፡ ኃጢአትየ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ወልደ፡ ሙሴ። ወኃጢአተ፡ ኲሉ፡ ሕዝብከ።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 74r: Lord our God, who destroyed the old wall of Jericho by the hand of Your servant Joshua, now in the same way destroy the wall of my sin, [the sin of] Your servant Wäldä Muse, and the sin of all Your people.</q>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#74v">Fol. 74v</locus>: A short sälam-hymn to the clergymen.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 74v: ሰላም፡ ለክሙ፡ ካህናት፡ አንትሙ፡ ለምግባረ፡ ሠናይ፡  ዘሃረየክሙ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ በሸርነቱ፡ ይምሀርክሙ፡ ለገቢረ፡ ፈቃዱ፡ ያክህልክሙ፡ አ{ፍ}ቅሩ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስትያን። ትሔይሰክሙ</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 74v: Peace be to you, priests! May the Lord, who has chosen you for good deeds, in His goodness teach you [and] enable you to perform His will. Love the Church which will be good for you.</q>
                           Written by Wäldä Muse.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Fol. 1r: Pen trial: “the pen which Wäldä Muse tried and began [writing with] on Monday, by the Lord’s grace”.&#xD;
- Fol. 74v: Writing exercise (beginning of the Ethiopic syllabary).&#xD;
- Fols. 83r (in the upper margin): 95r (in the bottom margin): The name በርናባስ፡ crudely written in pen.&#xD;
- Fols. 90v, 91r, 98r, 105r, 106r, 109r, 111v (in the bottom margin): Crude notes.&#xD;
- Fol. 104r (in the upper margin): በርናባስ፡ ተስፋየ፡ ፅገ፡ crudely written in pen; (in the bottom margin): ፅገ፡ ገ/ሚካኤል፡ crudely written in pen.&#xD;
- Fol. 110v (in the upper margin): pen trial. In the bottom margin: note.&#xD;
- Fol. 111r (in the upper margin): Note.</item>
                     </list>
